## üîç Part 4: 10 Basic SQL Commands with Output Examples

| SQL Command                                         | Example | Description                |
| --------------------------------------------------- | ------- | -------------------------- |
| `SHOW DATABASES;`                                   | ‚Äî       | Lists all databases        |
| `USE companydb;`                                    | ‚Äî       | Switch to companydb        |
| `SHOW TABLES;`                                      | ‚Äî       | Shows tables in current DB |
| `DESCRIBE employees;`                               | ‚Äî       | Shows table schema         |
| `SELECT * FROM employees;`                          | ‚Äî       | Show all rows              |
| `SELECT name FROM employees WHERE department='IT';` | ‚Äî       | Filter by condition        |
| `UPDATE employees SET salary=58000 WHERE id=5;`     | ‚Äî       | Update a row               |
| `DELETE FROM employees WHERE id=10;`                | ‚Äî       | Delete a row               |
| `ALTER TABLE employees ADD email VARCHAR(100);`     | ‚Äî       | Add new column             |
| `DROP TABLE employees;`                             | ‚Äî       | Delete table               |

